      id="projects.external.interpharm.claimSwitching.outputs.doc.architecture.introParagraph"&gt;
  In January 2005 Solms assessed the architecture used in a claim switching system. 
  The findings indicated that the there were opportunities for improving the reliability,
  maintainability and to some extend performance of the architecture by 
  <ns100:itemizedlist xmlns:ns100="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns101:listitem xmlns:ns101="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns102:para xmlns:ns102="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">simplifying the architecture,</ns102:para></ns101:listitem>
    <ns103:listitem xmlns:ns103="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns104:para xmlns:ns104="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">using a proven reference architecture for enterprise systems, and</ns104:para></ns103:listitem>
    <ns105:listitem xmlns:ns105="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns106:para xmlns:ns106="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">using standard proven tools.</ns106:para></ns105:listitem>
  </ns100:itemizedlist>
  Solms was thus commissioned to put a new architecture for the system in place without changing the
  design for the system. This document discusses
  <ns107:itemizedlist xmlns:ns107="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns108:listitem xmlns:ns108="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns109:para xmlns:ns109="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      the architectural drivers (<ns110:abbrev xmlns:ns110="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns110:abbrev> the quality requirements business places on the architecture)
      for the new architecture,
    </ns109:para></ns108:listitem>
    <ns111:listitem xmlns:ns111="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns112:para xmlns:ns112="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      the architectural patterns employed and the way in which these address some of the quality
      requirements,   
    </ns112:para></ns111:listitem>
    <ns113:listitem xmlns:ns113="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns114:para xmlns:ns114="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      architectural strategies used to realize the quality requirements,
    </ns114:para></ns113:listitem>
    <ns115:listitem xmlns:ns115="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns116:para xmlns:ns116="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      the choice of reference architecture and how the architectural patterns and strategies can be
      realized within the reference architecture,
    </ns116:para></ns115:listitem>
    <ns117:listitem xmlns:ns117="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns118:para xmlns:ns118="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      the core architectural components, the responsibilities they address and how they are
      realized,
    </ns118:para></ns117:listitem>
    <ns119:listitem xmlns:ns119="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns120:para xmlns:ns120="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      architectural risks as well as the trade-off decisions made, and
    </ns120:para></ns119:listitem>
    <ns121:listitem xmlns:ns121="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns122:para xmlns:ns122="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      the high-level architecture specification.
    </ns122:para></ns121:listitem>
  </ns107:itemizedlist>
</ns99:para>